00:08:44.040 --> 00:08:45.750
I always put a very simple title,

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:47.670
just saying the main niche of that book.

00:08:47.670 --> 00:08:49.800
And then in my subtitle,
I leave the opportunity

00:08:49.800 --> 00:08:51.690
to put in 3 related niches.

00:08:51.690 --> 00:08:54.030
So horses, horseback
riding and horse racing.

00:08:54.030 --> 00:08:56.490
I want to get as many
relevant keywords into

00:08:56.490 --> 00:08:58.350
that title without being too spammy to

00:08:58.350 --> 00:09:00.150
where Amazon wants it to
look more professional.

00:09:00.150 --> 00:09:01.740
And having 3 of them in here seems

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:03.180
to be the perfect happy medium.

00:09:03.180 --> 00:09:04.860
Now the last thing that
is really important

00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:06.240
to know is your description.

00:09:06.240 --> 00:09:08.250
You want to make sure that you
have keywords throughout your

00:09:08.250 --> 00:09:09.300
description as well.

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:11.640
I have a specific process
that I used to create all

00:09:11.640 --> 00:09:12.900
of my descriptions and make sure

00:09:12.900 --> 00:09:14.100
that I have keywords throughout it.

00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:15.840
If you do want to learn this process

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:18.450
and everything else that
I do for Amazon, KDP,

00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:21.210
